#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:4
msgid ""
"Profiling is a key step for performance optimization. You can build MLX with "
"the ``MLX_METAL_DEBUG`` option to improve the Metal debugging and "
"optimization workflow. The ``MLX_METAL_DEBUG`` debug option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:8
msgid ""
"Records source during Metal compilation, for later inspection while "
"debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:10
msgid ""
"Labels Metal objects such as command queues, improving capture readability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:12
msgid ""
"The ``metal::start_capture`` function initiates a capture of all MLX GPU "
"work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:14
msgid ""
"int main() {\n"
"    metal::start_capture(\"/Users/Jane/Developer/MLX.gputrace\");\n"
"\n"
"    auto a = arange(10.f, 20.f, 1.f, float32);\n"
"    auto b = arange(30.f, 40.f, 1.f, float32);\n"
"    auto c = add(a, b);\n"
"\n"
"    eval(c);\n"
"\n"
"    metal::stop_capture();\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/dev/metal_debugger.rst:28
msgid ""
